article.headline: North Texas 83, UT-Chattanooga 76
article.story: DENTON, Texas (AP) -- Kendrick Davis scored 20 points and Michael Sturns added 19 as North Texas rallied in the second half to beat Chattanooga 83-76 Saturday night. The Mean Green (2-2) trailed 42-35 at halftime but outscored Chattanooga 48-34 in the second half. Chattanooga (1-5) made 7 of 13 3-pointers in the first half but cooled off after halftime, making just 3 of 10. Davis was 6-of-16 from the field but made all six of his free throws. Sturns was 7-of-12, including 3-of-5 from 3-point range. Keddric Mays was one of four Chattanooga players in double figures with 19 points. He was joined by Alphonso Pugh (12), Nicchaeus Doaks (11) and Charles Anderson (10). Pugh had 11 rebounds. Jeffrey Simpson had 9 points and 11 rebounds for North Texas.
